<br>
    It would be relatively easy to implement, and would give mags a very good reason to get into endgame raids.  Flags exist for spells that can or can't be cast in a zone, and possibly even in a given location in a given zone.  This idea would make us the premiere Summoners in the game, and would also allow alternative grouping configurations besides the traditional melee/cleric/enchanter paradigm.<br>
<br>
    Food for thought. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 820<br> <font color=#333333>(2/13/02 9:55:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=296.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: New pet ideas</span><hr size=1> An even easier idea to implement would be to add pet only weapons that drop as loot, and add to stats, especially attack.  Presumably they would be too expensive to use when soloing or in groups, and would be consumed when the pet dispersed.  These pet only weapons could drop off raid mobs, and thus only obtainable by guilds, which would limit their use further.  This would also allow <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to control their introduction into the game, and simply cease the drops if it turned out to be too powerful.<br>
